---
import PageLayout from '@layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { site } from '@data/site';

const lastUpdated = 'June 2026';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How allaiamedia.com handles your data."
  eyebrow={`Last updated · ${lastUpdated}`}
  heading="Privacy."
  italic=""
  lead="Short version — we collect the minimum we need to publish, ship a book, run a small private practice, and send a slow newsletter. We do not sell your data. Here is the long version, in plain English."
  byline={`Questions — ${site.email}`}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-6 prose-essay">
    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>ALLAIA Media (referred to as "we", "us", or "ALLAIA Media") is the operational entity behind allaiamedia.com, Allaia Power as a personal brand, the book Become Her, The Architecture (1:1 private practice), and Coven (community, launching Q3 2026). We are the controller of any personal data you share with us via this site or in the course of working together.</p>
    <p>Reach us about anything privacy-related at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>

    <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
    <h3>When you visit allaiamedia.com</h3>
    <p>Basic analytics — page views, referrers, country, device type — through a privacy-respecting analytics provider that does not track you across other sites. Server logs (IP address, timestamp, request path) retained for thirty days for security and debugging.</p>

    <h3>When you contact us or apply</h3>
    <p>Stan Store handles book purchases and The Architecture applications — your purchase data is processed by Stan Store under their privacy policy. Newsletter signups are handled by our newsletter provider. Email and Instagram DMs sit with their respective providers.</p>

    <h3>When you join the private practice</h3>
    <p>Name, billing details, and the content of our work together (calls, written threads, journaling shared with permission). All of this is treated as confidential by default.</p>

    <h2>3. Why we collect it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to your inquiry, run a discovery call, and deliver the work (contract / legitimate interest).</li>
      <li>To invoice you and meet our tax and legal obligations (legal obligation).</li>
      <li>To improve the site and understand which writing lands (legitimate interest).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Who we share it with</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent your data. We use a focused set of trusted processors to operate the business — each bound by a data-processing agreement:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Hosting — Cloudflare Pages.</li>
      <li>Storefront — Stan Store (book + The Architecture application).</li>
      <li>Newsletter — Beehiiv (or current provider — see the signup form).</li>
      <li>Email — Google Workspace.</li>
      <li>Messaging — Instagram (Meta).</li>
      <li>Accounting — standard cloud accounting platform under DPA.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. How long we keep it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Inquiries that do not convert — deleted after twelve months.</li>
      <li>Active client data — kept for the duration of our work plus seven years for legal / accounting reasons.</li>
      <li>Server logs — thirty days.</li>
      <li>Analytics — aggregated, no individual retention.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
    <p>Wherever you are based, you can ask us to see what data we hold about you, correct anything that is wrong, delete it (subject to legal-hold periods), stop processing it for marketing, or export it in a portable format. Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> and we will respond within thirty days. If you are in the EU or UK, you also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data-protection authority.</p>

    <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
    <p>We use the minimum cookies needed to run the site. No third-party advertising cookies. No cross-site tracking. Your browser settings let you block or delete any cookies you do not want.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>If we change anything material, we update the date at the top and post the new version here. Significant changes get an email to anyone we have worked with directly.</p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
